pulfalight.title: Users should be able to search by collection identifiers
Update the indexing procedures for the ArchivesSpace EADs
Integrate the Aeon REST API for supporting requests

comments.body: The latest Aeon API is exposed on https://lib-aeon.princeton.edu/aeon/api and documented using https://lib-aeon.princeton.edu/aeon/api/swagger/. Please be aware that the credentials for authenticating for requests is stored in LastPass.

I am failing to retrieve resources and receiving a 401 response from requests which use the API token provided in LastPass:

```
> GET /aeon/api/Queues/ HTTP/1.1
> Host: lib-aeon.princeton.edu
> User-Agent: curl/7.54.0
> Accept: */*
> Content-Type: application/json
> Authorization: Bearer [SECRET]
>
< HTTP/1.1 401 Unauthorized
< Cache-Control: must-revalidate
< Pragma: no-cache
< Expires: 0
< Server: Kestrel
< X-Powered-By: ASP.NET
< Date: Mon, 20 Jul 2020 19:38:32 GMT
< Content-Length: 0
```

The new API seems responsive for unauthenticated requests, however, reviewing the Aeon API documentation, there does not seem to be an API for `POST` requesting new requests. This would block the support of the new Aeon API until this is supported.
Following #314, this should only be scoped for testing against the legacy endpoint `https://lib-aeon.princeton.edu/aeon/Aeon.dll`
